OL,3,CShoplifting driving abuse of retail
OL,4,Cworkers as 69% report threats at work
OL,6,FFigures released by the ONS in October
OL,7,Fhave shown more than 469,000
OL,8,Fshoplifting offences were recorded
OL,9,Fbetween June 2023 and June 2024 - up
OL,10,Ffrom around 365,000 incidents the year
OL,11,Fbefore. This marks the highest figure
OL,12,Fsince current police recording
OL,13,Fpractices began.
OL,15,FThose who contributed to the USDAW's
OL,16,Fsurvey reported being hit with
OL,17,Ftrollies, scratched, sworn at, pushed
OL,18,Fagainst walls, held at knife point and
OL,19,Fsexually assaulted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
