OL,3,CShoplifting driving abuse of retail
OL,4,Cworkers as 69% report threats at work
OL,6,FPaddy Lillis, who leads the union,
OL,7,Fsaid experiencing repeated theft and
OL,8,Flooting can leave retail workers left
OL,9,Fwith "anxiety, fear and in some cases
OL,10,Fphysical harm".
OL,12,FMr Lillis added: "It has become
OL,13,Fincreasingly common for retail stores
OL,14,Fto be targeted by organised crime
OL,15,Fgangs stealing to order in the midst
OL,16,Fof a retail crime epidemic."
